4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO PUBLIC CHARGING STATIONS
5 FOR ELECTRIC VEHICLES; CLARIFYING PUBLIC CHARGING STATION TAX PROVISIONS; REVISING
6 ELECTRIC METER REQUIREMENTS; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; AMENDING SECTIONS 15-70-801, 15-
7 70-802, 15-70-803, 15-70-804, AND 15-70-805, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 15-70-801, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "15-70-801. Definitions. As used in this part, unless the context clearly indicates otherwise, the
13 following definitions apply:
14 (1) "Charging station" means equipment with a rated capacity greater than 25 kilowatts that is not
15 installed at a residence or owned by an association of real property owners including a homeowners'
16 association as defined in 70-17-901 that transfers electric current to the power system of an electric vehicle and
17 the real property in to which the equipment is affixed, and includes a public charging stationstations and public
18 legacy charging stations.
19 (2) "Charging station operator" means a person, firm, general partnership, limited partnership,
20 limited liability partnership, corporation, limited liability company, or other lawfully recognized business entity
21 that operates a public charging station.
22 (3) "Charging station owner" means the entity that is the public utility customer or a public utility
23 that owns a public charging station.
24 (3)(4) "Public charging station" means a charging station that is a business using a metered system
25 to deliver that delivers electric current to an electric vehicle and charges the customer either for the electricity
26 transferred or for the duration of time during which the transfer of electricity takes place.
27 (4) "Public legacy charging station" means a public charging station operating before July 1, 2023,
28 that has never had a metering system in place capable of measuring electricity transferred from the charging
