5 Section 2. Section 15-70-802, MCA, is amended to read:
6 "15-70-802. Public charging station tax -- public legacy charging station tax -- reduction of
7 additional electric vehicle registration fees. (1) Effective July 1, 2023, there There is a tax of 3 cents a
8 kilowatt hour or its equivalent in addition to the public utility's approved rate on the electric current used to
9 charge or recharge the battery or batteries of an electric vehicle at public charging stations installed after July 1,
10 2023 on electricity delivered to a public charging station.
11 (2) Effective July 1, 2025, there is a tax of 3 cents a kilowatt hour or its equivalent in addition to the
12 public utility's approved rate on the electric current used to charge or recharge the battery or batteries of an
13 electric vehicle at public legacy charging stations.
14 (3)(2) The tax authorized by this section is based on the rate of tax and electricity transferred during
15 the charging process, and it does not include any fees or charges associated with the method of payment for
16 the charging services in addition to the public utility's rate and measured at the utility's meter.
17 (4)(3) Effective July 1, 2028, the amount of any additional electric vehicle registration fee charged by
18 the state to a resident on an electric vehicle is reduced by 30%."
19
20 Section 3. Section 15-70-803, MCA, is amended to read:
21 "15-70-803. Installation of electric meters. (1) Effective July 1, 2023, all new All public charging
22 stations must have an a separate electric meter installed or approved by the public utility exclusively dedicated
23 to the public charging station that measures all of the electricity delivered to the public charging station. The
24 charging station owner shall pay the cost of meter installation.
25 (2) Effective July 1, 2025, all public charging stations and public legacy charging stations installed
26 prior to July 1, 2023, must have an electric meter installed or approved by the public utility exclusively dedicated
27 to the public charging station or public legacy charging station that measures all of the electricity delivered to
28 the public charging station or public legacy charging station. The charging station owner shall pay the cost of
